cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.CY 

This paper deals with recommending emotionally pleasant routes in the city, which involves analyzing crowd-sourced data and image metadata. This suggests that it could fall under the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), and Computers and Society (cs.CY). Among these, cs.SI and cs.HC are the most likely as they deal with user behavior and interaction with technology.
